The style of Berserk is a mix of Lovecraftian horror and the beauty of Kentaro Miura's hand. When I flip the page of a physical copy it's almost like I'm witnessing a painting. Miura's work really pulls you in, and it get's better over the years. When you start reading the first volume of Berserk you'l be tugged at, by the 6th volume you'l be grasped and pulled under.\
